<TITLE> First-ever laptop fair kicks off </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 25 (bdnews24.com)  A three-day laptop fair styled the 'Laptop Party-2008' began Friday at the Bangladesh-China Friendship Conference Centre. Laptops priced from as low as Tk 27,000 are on sale at the first-of-its-kind fair. Education adviser Hossain Zillur Rahman who inaugurated the event said the government would continue to provide all cooperation to develop the science and technology sector. "We have a lot more to achieve, especially in the field of information technology," he added. The fair's organisers, non-governmental organisation Maker Communications, said they expected visitors to attend in increasing numbers over the three days. The inauguration was attended by Secretary to the Chief Adviser Kazi Aminul Islam, Better Business Forum member and former Tariff Commission chairman Dr MA Taslim, Better Business Forum member Syed Mahmudul Huq and Bangladesh Computer Society president Mostafa Jabbar. bdnews24.
